The article is a statement by the Press Secretary on the meeting of the two Cypriot leaders, Mr. Nicos Anastasiades and Mr. Dervish Eroglu, and the renewal of negotiations on a Cyprus settlement under the auspices of the United Nations. The statement welcomes the meeting and the spirit of compromise shown by the leaders. It also acknowledges the constructive role played by Turkey, Greece, and other international parties in the effort. The United States encourages the sides to work expeditiously to resolve outstanding core issues and achieve a settlement that reunifies Cyprus as a bi-zonal, bi-communal federation. The statement also supports President Anastasiades' proposals for confidence-building measures and other constructive initiatives to enhance cooperation between the communities. The United States reaffirms its support for the sovereign rights of the Republic of Cyprus and emphasizes the importance of upholding peace and security in the region.